items.name: C-3PO from "Star Wars"
items.description:
After 110 models, 448 hours of processing, 2500 likes and 18K downloads, I want to sincerely thank the 5 people in total who supported me.

The model removed by Civitai will be reposted with "non-sexy" showcase.

C-3PO is a humanoid robot character in the Star Wars franchise who appears in the original trilogy, the prequel trilogy and the sequel trilogy. Built by Anakin Skywalker, C-3PO was designed as a protocol droid intended to assist in etiquette, customs, and translation,] boasting that he is "fluent in over six million forms of communication". Along with his astromech droid counterpart and friend R2-D2, C-3PO provides comic relief within the narrative structure of the films, and serves as a foil. Anthony Daniels has portrayed the character in eleven of the twelve theatrical Star Wars films released to date, with the exception of Solo: A Star Wars Story, where the character does not appear.

Despite his oblivious nature, C-3PO has played a pivotal role in the galaxy's history, appearing under the service of Shmi Skywalker, the Lars homestead, Padm√© Amidala, Bail Organa, Raymus Antilles, Luke Skywalker, Jabba the Hutt, and Leia Organa. In the majority of depictions, C-3PO's physical appearance is primarily a polished gold plating with a silver plated right leg (from knee joint to ankle), although its appearance varies throughout the films; including the absence of metal coverings in The Phantom Menace, a dull copper plating in Attack of the Clones, and a red left arm in The Force Awakens. C-3PO also appears frequently in both canon and Star Wars Legends continuities of novels, comic books, and video games, and was a protagonist in the animated television series Droids.

Part three of a LoRA set dedicated to small breasted women. Puffy nipples come on all breast sizes, but this set is specially trained on small boobs.

items.name: Nocturian Greco/roman fantasy Soldier by Paradigme
items.description:
"While every civilization inhabits the world of Landhelven, they are more or less dominated by the Nocturian Empire, the pinnacle of nations and a symbol of power. The majority of the continent belongs to them, although the lands of Austermors remain mysterious and unconquered in their eyes. The Nocturians are skilled diplomats, yet they are renowned for their flawless military and political strategies. When they desire something, they always find a way to obtain it. Fortunately, their ideals are founded on cooperation with other peoples, spending more time on trade than conquest, although conflicts with the Estarsitz prove otherwise. They are typically clad in lightweight garments such as togas or draped attire, varying by region, but their armor is well-crafted to allow freedom of movement. The distinctive green crested helm signifies their affiliation with the Nocturians. They primarily worship Nocturia, the goddess of night, seasons, and balance, yet they have always shown great tolerance towards other religions."

-----------------------------------------

Here's an AI model that allows you to generate members of a Greco/roman fantasy. It was specifically designed to illustrate the Nocturians, a people in my role-playing game universe "Landhelven."

I recommend using the trigger words "Nocturien" and "warrior," but you can replace "warrior" with other professions.

I hope you enjoy using this model. Please feel free to provide feedback on its strengths and weaknesses.

Introduction

This is my third release after long testing with LoRA generation. I hope you like her.

I am planing to release other LoRA with similar tags in the future so you can mix different shapes and create new styles.

Training Data

This LoRA was trained with close up images of similar pussy to get a consistent look.

Image count: 67

Resolution: 512x768

I will probably update her in the future as I got more images I wan't to include.

Model

LazyMix+ (Real Amateur Nudes) v2

I might train this LoRA on other models too to see if the results will be better. For now it seems that only this model can be used for generation so don't waste your time with others.

For inpainting use the same model but converted it to an inpaint version with the checkpoint merger of webui. Inpainting this LoRA without an inpainting model will be hard.

Don't forget to switch back to the regular model if you get weird results. Happens to me all the time when I start a new image. The inpaining model can not produce normal images.

Tags

pussy_butterfly_small - Main tag

butterfly pussy - Labia is spread like a butterfly

butthole - Changes poses so buttholes are better visible

photo - Training image was a real photo

rendering - Training image was generated with an earlier LoRA version (experimental)

How to use

DPM++SDE Karras: More realistic images

Euler a: Smoother images

Use 512x768 for image size and upscale later.

CFG scale depends on the tags you are using. Anywhere in the range from 2 to 6 should work. Lower values are better.

Try to avoid Restore Faces if possible as it will sometimes changes the pussy to some kind of weird face or adds teeth.

For basic close up images just add the LoRA + pussy_butterfly_small tag. For more tags see the LoRA metadata. If you add too much tags the result may get worse.

For body shots you need to lower the LoRA strenght but this will reduce pussy details. I try to use the Regional Prompter extension so I can keep the strenght higher. Fix anything with inpainting that you don't like. Or just create an image without the LoRA and inpaint the pussy with LoRA afterwards.

Also works good to inpaint on real HD images to replace a pussy. This was the primary purpose why I created this LoRA.

The close up sample images are created by txt2img without editing. The full body images are completely inpainted from real images.

Upscaling

For best results I am using ControlNet with type tile + Ultimate SD upscale to keep the image stable without adding ghost pussy all over the place. Upscale 2-3x works most of the time.

items.name: RockyKemono (furry & kemono mix)
items.description:
About:
I made this because other models weren't really working for me. Maybe it was a skill issue or me not being good with tags, no idea. Anyway, I present you RockyKemono (very original name, I know), a mix of Fluffyrock, CrossKemono and BB. Works great for SFW and NSFW.

Things to remember:
1) Use e621 tags (really, don't even try going for Danbooru style). You can make your life easier by using the tag autocomplete extension for Automatic1111 WebUI and loading the FluffyRock tagset
2) Experimenting with different artists available on e6 is encouraged. Be sure to preceed artist tag with "by" (by chelodoy, by tsampikos, by zeekzag, by kappadoggo, by pgm3000, etc)
3) Mix doesn't have a baked in VAE. I recommed using kl-f8-anime2 or ClearVAEv2.3 but you can use any VAE you like
4) All LORAs I threw at the mix worked fine so you can go wild with them

What's inside:
fluffyrock-576-704-832-960-1088-lion-low-lr-e27-offset-noise-e12
bb95FurryMix_v50
crosskemono_v2.5
a tiny model I worked on and never released (based on art from my friends)

I might continue working on this merge later but it's more than fine for my cooming needs for now. If you have any suggestions on how to improve it let me know.
Aight, working on a new version based on the 3M branch of FluffyRock. Wish me luck.

items.name: Delorean-Arnie
items.description:
And there is another LoRA from the Delorean series (80's retro). This time the mighty Arnie has shot his way to you and slashed his sword! It took me a lot of practice, but I finally managed to cram all of Arnold's important characters from the 80's into one LoRA. So say hello to Conan, Dutch, the Matrix and the T-800.

Also... If you like my work, I'd be glad if you would tip it with a small amount to help me partially cover my expenses with Google Colab. Thanks a lot! https://ko-fi.com/stepaan

How to:

LoRA contains three main trigger words:

  • arnie_conan: Arnie as Conan ;-)

  • arnie_term: Arnie as Terminator ;-)

  • arnie_soldier: This is actually a mix of his characters from Predator, Commando and Red Heat.

There's one in the sample pictures that shows that even as little as typing one of these trigger words into a positive prompts pushes the LoRA straight to work.

Then there are other tags like:

  • Conan: headband, sword, necklace

  • Terminator: holding gun, sunglasses

  • Soldier: facial camouflage, military vest, holding gun, holding rocket launcher (but take this one with a grain of salt, he's not very good at it).

  • Use them as positive or negative.

Settings:

As always, I recommend AnalogMadness or another checkpoint with as little custom handwriting as possible. Keep the prompts as simple as possible (unless you find a complex one that works). Use HiresFix and forget Face Restore.

Strength: 1, cfg: 5, steps: 20+
